    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Wellington</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cox</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 22, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Refer Department’s November 13, 11 p.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d575fn16">Not
                        printed.</note> It is Department’s understanding that arrangements being
                    worked out by General Short and Air Commodore Saunders will include through
                    flights to be made by United States service aircraft over New Zealand territory
                    or mandated islands. It is understood that this is agreeable to New Zealand
                    military authorities. Please mention matter in strict confidence to appropriate
                    high officer of New Zealand Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
